Part 6: PGVector

You are storing embeddings in PostgreSQL.

Normally PostgreSQL stores:

Text
Integer
Date

PGVector allows:

Vectors

Example:

[0.12,0.34,-0.22...]

⸻

Table:

CREATE TABLE pgvector_store

Contains:

Column	Meaning
doc_id	document identifier
content	chunk text
embedding	vector
mail_ref_id	reference
attachment_id	file
content_hash	duplicate detection

⸻

Part 7: Duplicate Logic

You added:

content_hash

Generated using:

SHA256

Example:

Text:

Policy Number: 123

Hash:

A8D92JDKS...

⸻

Purpose:

Avoid storing same chunk again.

⸻

Example:

Document uploaded again.

Same text.

Same hash.

System checks:

chunk_exists()

If exists:

Skip insertion

⸻

Without this:

Database becomes:

Policy Number
Policy Number
Policy Number
Policy Number

Many duplicates.

