Part 8: Why Chunk Similarity Search Works

Imagine database contains:

Chunk A

Named Insured ABC

Chunk B

Policy Number POL123

Chunk C

Limit 1,000,000

Each chunk has embedding.

⸻

User asks:

Policy ID

Convert question to embedding.

Now PGVector calculates distance.

Conceptually:

Question Vector
     ↓
Chunk A distance = 0.8
Chunk B distance = 0.1
Chunk C distance = 0.9

Smaller distance = more similar.

Therefore:

Chunk B returned

